com.avaya.cmapi

Class ServiceProviderAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.avaya.cmapi.ServiceProviderAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ServiceProviderListener, java.util.EventListener

    public class ServiceProviderAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements ServiceProviderListener
    Implements a "do nothing" callback method for each service provider event type. To learn more about how to use a listener adapter, see Using Listeners in the Device, Media & Call Control (DMCC) API.

    • Method Detail

      • serverConnectionDown

        public void serverConnectionDown(ServerConnectionDownEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: ServiceProviderListener
        Callback method that is called when the connection to the CMAPI server goes down. Any time during the active session, if the connection to the CMAPI server goes down, this callback method is called. Also when the reconnect fails, this callback method is called too. See the ServerConnectionDownEvent for more information. To recover from this ServerConnectionDownEvent, the application can call ServiceProvider().reconnect to reconnect and resume the session. The ServerConnectionDownEvent contains reason why the connection is down and exceptions if any.
        Specified by:
        serverConnectionDown in interface ServiceProviderListener
        Parameters:
        event - an indication that the connection to the server is down. Use event.getReason() or event.getException() to determine the cause of the failure.

      • serverSessionNotActive

        public void serverSessionNotActive(ServerSessionNotActiveEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: ServiceProviderListener
        Callback method that is called when the session for the Service Provider is in an inactive state. This event will happen when any message is sent to the CMAPI server but the session is inactive. This includes heartbeat messages that are sent to the server based on the session duration timer which was set by the property cmapi.session_duration_timer. See the ServerSessionNotActiveEvent for more information. The ServerSessionNotActiveEvent contains reason why the session is not active.
        Specified by:
        serverSessionNotActive in interface ServiceProviderListener
        Parameters:
        event - an indication that the session is not active. Use event.getReason() or event.getCode() to determine the cause of the failure.

      • serverSessionTerminated

        public void serverSessionTerminated(ServerSessionTerminatedEvent event)
        Description copied from interface: ServiceProviderListener
        Callback method that is called when the session for the Service Provider is terminated. This event will occur if the user has requested session termination via the ServiceProvider().disconnect method, or when any message is sent to the CMAPI server but the session has been terminated. This includes heartbeat messages that are sent to the server based on the session duration timer which was set by the property cmapi.session_duration_timer. See the ServerSessionTerminatedEvent for more information. The ServerSessionTerminatedEvent contains reason why the session is terminated.
        Specified by:
        serverSessionTerminated in interface ServiceProviderListener
        Parameters:
        event - an indication that the session is terminated. Use event.getReason() or event.getCode() to determine the cause of the failure.
